name: xcb-proto
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set xorg_name = "xcb-proto" %}
{% set xorg_category = "xcb" %}
{% set name = "xcb-proto" %}
{% set version = "1.13" %}
{% set sha256 = "7b98721e669be80284e9bbfeab02d2d0d54cd11172b72271e47a2fe875e2bde1" %}
{% set am_version = "1.15" %} # keep synchronized with build.sh

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ xorg_name }}-{{ version }}.tar.bz2
  url: https://www.x.org/releases/individual/{{ xorg_category }}/{{ xorg_name }}-{{ version }}.tar.bz2
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}
  patches:
    - windows-pythondir.patch  # [win]
    - fix-deprecated-gcd.patch

build:
  number: 1010
  detect_binary_files_with_prefix: true

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - m2-autoconf                   # [win]
    - m2-automake{{ am_version }}   # [win]
    - m2-libtool                    # [win]
    - m2w64-pkg-config              # [win]
    - pkg-config                    # [not win]
    - posix                         # [win]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}           # [unix]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}     # [win]
    - make                          # [unix]
    - autoconf                      # [unix]
    - automake                      # [unix]
    - gettext                       # [unix]
    - libtool                       # [unix]
  host:
    - python
    - xorg-util-macros
  run:
    - python

test:
  requires:
    - m2w64-pkg-config  # [win]
    - pkg-config        # [not win]
  imports:
    - xcbgen
  commands:
    - pkg-config --variable=pythondir xcb-proto  # [not win]
    - set "PKG_CONFIG_PATH=%LIBRARY_LIB%\pkgconfig" && pkg-config --variable=pythondir xcb-proto  # [win]

about:
  home: http://xcb.freedesktop.org/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: COPYING
  summary: "Provides the XML-XCB protocol descriptions that libxcb uses to generate the majority of its code and API"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ccordoba12
    - mingwandroid
    - pkgw
